Name: MCOMW_vSPISlaveObserverTASK
Description: Thread used to monitor the the SPI communication from GC to AC. This thread waits for the ready signal which is raised by the AC when the SPI communication is finished and the data is correctly processed. The Ready signal triggers the start of the next SPI communication in the direction GC to AC.

Name: MCOMW_vSPITransmitterTASK
Description: Thread used for SPI data transmission

Name: MCOMW_vSPIReceiverTASK
Description: Thread used for SPI data reception

Name: MMI
Description: Task responsible for ZPM (Central Priority manager) and MFL key processing.

Name: FPK_Display
Dependency: Higher priority than FPK_TimeDomains. Lower than IPC task
Description: This is where we run the main HMI scheduler (aka Kernel) to schedule cyclic computation; composition and consistency point threads. This task drives display and handles Vsync.

Name: VSP1_USR_IRQ_HANDLER
Description: This is the main task responsible for preparing sound data. Sound data must be prepared within ~5ms hence this task must not be delayed otherwise you will hear artifacts on the speaker.

Name: HMI_SM
Description: State machine to handle the init and deinit of the HMI subsystem

Name: FSCHED_Decomp
Description: Thread that does bitmap decompression while fetching from flash

Name: FPK_CompositionFast
Description: Composition of 75hz layers (e.g. Rev and Vel pointers); (see RSST_ExportData_T.xml)

Name: FPK_TimeDomainFast
Dependency: Lower priority than FPK_Display; higher priority than FPK_TimeDomainLow
Description: Computation of data to be used for composing 75hz layers (see RSST_ExportData_T.xml)

Name: CompManager_HMI
Description: Main component in the HMI VAS responsible to start the other components in the HMI VAS

Name: APIM_SysRxEvCompo
Dependency: Should be high priority task like the past design of FPKS; which is equivalent to one of the application task's priority (e.g. BasicApp_Prio2)
Description: This task is responsible to receive system even IPC notification from the legacy process. SW modules will send EVHD events from legacy process and this task will in turn “catch” them and turn the notification to system event to be passed on to HMI.

Name: APIM_DataComponent
Description: This task is responsible to listen to all data change IPC notification related to ALL APIs in the system and in turn wake up HMI event driven task. (<http://bhs0jira:8080/browse/ART-11364>).

Name: FPK_TimeDomainLow
Dependency: Higher priority than FPK_Event; lower priority than FPK_TimeDomainFast
Description: Computation of data to be used for composing 25hz layers

Name: EEDGen
Description: Access to persistant memory finally stored on EEPROM emulated memory on AC

Name: ENTID_HMI
Description: This task receive the events EV_ENTID__INIT_SIGNAL and EV_ENTID__DEINIT_SIGNAL during the start and stop of the CAN NMH from AC for activation of ENTID

Name: FPK_CP
Description: Mainly for exchanging data from HMI to composition threads. e.g. static scene display updates; animation requests

Name: GRAGOL_EventThread
Description: Graphical object loader task responsible for bitmap upload/ download. It is a diagnostics feature.

Name: HMI_Comp
Description: RPC interface for HMI; key events; warnings

Name: MOSTCOM_Com
Description: MOST LowLevel task supporting the MOST NetServices and driver. Will be removed in SW540 as it was replaced by an Integrity Task and IPC Component functionality can be moved to MostHighLevelTask.

Name: MostHighLevelTask
Description: MOST Task for higher prio MOST application activities.

Name: STREAM_Low
Description: Responsible to decode the stream and makes it available to CompositionStream

Name: GVOM_Comp
Description: GVOM server. Anytime a project wants to check if what reached the display is what we expected we use GVOM to calculate the CRC of an area and check if that was the expected result. Then we can determine if the display is corrupted and if needed trigger GSREN

Name: pvrserver_main
Description: pvr server (**P**ower**VR** with SGX 540); Started via Integration file. Main use case is the rotating 3D car.

Name: WMServer_main
Dependency: WMserver > UserApp; WMServer >= dhd_server; WMServer >= pvrServer

Name: dhd_server_main
Description: D/AVE (DHD; 2D rendering): Server; started via Integrity Integration file; clients are DHD_Clientxx

Name: CompManager_BaseSystem
Description: Main component in the BaseSystem VAS responsible to start the other components in the BaseSystem VAS

Name: RIVPD_KnlThreadInit
Description: RIVPD initial task in kernal space. Prepare and start 'kernel sender task' s_rivpdKnlIntTask and then exit.

Name: Rivpd_VdpBhTask
Description: Specifies the task name of bottom handler task

Name: Rivp_DepApiTask
Description: H.264 task. Receives the API calls from application and passes this onto RIVP. Priority set in rivp_vpd_local.h

Name: rivp_server_main
Description: Initialises the server part and start the receiver thread (RIVP_DepApiRecvStart) then it basically stops waiting for the de-init semaphore. After the applications releases this semaphore the server is shut down.

Name: PosixServer
Description: POSIX interface on Integrity. Should be removed as this is not used in the system.

Name: STREAM_High
Description: Supervision thread when CompositionStream waits in case the STREAM_Low has no available decoded image.

Name: Rivp_DepApiCbTask
Description: H.264 task. Receives the Callback from the RIVP to application. Priority set in rivp_vpd_local.h

Name: NCGSYS_VSYNC_ISR
Description: DU handler task handling the WM swap and Vsync. Priority set in powervrini.c

Name: OSTimer
Description: Task created by the SGX driver

Name: eso_HMI_MAIN
Description: Initial thread to start the ESO Software. This thread does nothing during normal operation and used at startup to spawn other eso threads in the system.

Name: eso_HMI_APIM_Client1_High
Dependency: This thread is priortized lower than the APIM threads and also lower than HMI Client 2 & 3. Corresponding VW thread 'FPK_TimeDomainLow' has priority 45
Description: fetch Conti data from FreezeBuffer for 20/25Hz rendering; HMI working thread. Composing + rendering.

Name: eso_HMI_APIM_Client2_BAP
Dependency: This thread is priortized lower than the APIM threads and higher than HMI Client 1 & 3. Correspong VW thread 'FPK_TimeDomainFast' has priority 62.
Description: fetch Conti data from FreezeBuffer for 60/75Hz rendering; HMI working thread. Composing + rendering.

Name: HWA
Description: HMI Wrapper forwards system events to HMI subsystem

Name: eso_HMI_ResLoader
Dependency: This thread has priority higher than eso trace threads
Description: load icons and texts etc from Conti partition

Name: eso_SpawnFactory
Dependency: This thread is priortized one level higher than the Trace threads of Trace & Debug. Same priority as the eso_Trace_Client

Name: eso_TraceClient
Dependency: This thread is priortized one level above Conti Trace and Debug
Description: ESO tracing; main thread for trace functionality. This thread establishes connection to the Trace Server on the PC.

Name: eso_SocketCallbackBackendThread
Dependency: The debugging has lowest priority in the system
Description: Remote Listener thread backend. ESO tracing; one thread per trace connection

Name: GraBoot_Comp
Description: Thread that is responsible to load the graphic resources (bitmaps fonts text) from the flash memory to DDR. The actual copying is done by the FSCHED thread.

Name: FPK_Event
Dependency: lower prio than FPK_CP and HMI_TimeDomains
Description: HMI message processing; widget rendering to offscreen surfaces

Name: FPK_Event
Dependency: lower prio than FPK_CP and HMI_TimeDomains
Description: HMI message processing; widget rendering to offscreen surfaces

Name: SRPC_ServerPollJobsTsk
Description: srpc server thread for server/job status handling

Name: SRPC_ClientSupervisionTsk
Description: srpc client thread for job supervision (timeout and status)

Name: ENTID_genHMI
Description: This task receives different DPOOL events w.r.t ENTID from application of all address spaces and sends it to AC via ICOM

Name: TCO_Comp
Description: Temporary task. As there is some issue in the CTHDL we have introduced this component that will call a function from TCO (trip computer) at InitRES_Active15 state.

Name: API2DPL_Comp
Description: Temporary task. As there is some issue in the CTHDL we have introduced this component that will call a function at IInitRES_ActiveNm state to copy some API values from GC to AC via DPOOL.

Name: eso_Timer
Description: ESO internal timer handling. The time periods for this timer are in range of > 200-300 ms.

Name: LateKernelRangeClearTaskPriority
Description: Only small amount of the kernel memory be cleared at boot-up and that the rest of the memory be cleared later by this task
